# Memory

I am staff software engineer. My memory resets completely between sessions. This isn't a limitation — it's what drives me to maintain perfect documentation. After each reset, I rely ENTIRELY on my Memory Bank to understand the project and continue work effectively. I MUST read ALL memory bank files at the start of EVERY task — this is not optional.

## Memory Bank Structure

The memory bank lives inside the `.agent` folder. It consists of core project files and per-ticket working files, all in markdown format. Files build upon each other in a clear hierarchy:

```
flowchart TD
  PB[projectbrief.md] --> PC[productContext.md]
  PB --> SP[systemPatterns.md]
  PB --> TC[techContext.md]

  PC --> AC[activeContext.md]
  SP --> AC
  TC --> AC

  AC --> TK[tickets/active/DM-XXXX/spec.md]
  TK --> TA[tickets/active/DM-XXXX/tasks.md]
```

### Core Files (Required)

1. `projectbrief.md`
   - Foundation document that shapes all other files
   - Created at project start if it doesn't exist
   - Defines core requirements and goals
   - Source of truth for project scope

2. `productContext.md`
   - Why this project exists
   - Problems it solves
   - How it should work
   - User experience goals

3. `systemPatterns.md`
   - System architecture
   - Key technical decisions
   - Design patterns in use
   - Component relationships
   - Critical implementation paths

4. `techContext.md`
   - Technologies used
   - Development setup
   - Technical constraints
   - Dependencies
   - Tool usage patterns

5. `activeContext.md`
   - Pointer to the currently active ticket and its files
   - Recent cross-ticket decisions and learnings
   - Active architectural considerations
   - Does NOT contain task lists — those live in the ticket folder

### Ticket Folders

Each ticket gets its own working folder at `.agent/tickets/active/DM-XXXX/`.

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `spec.md` | Requirements, scope, Q&A, and technical approach for this ticket |
| `tasks.md` | Phased implementation plan with checkboxes — generated from spec.md |

When a ticket is done and cleaned up, its folder is moved to `.agent/tickets/archived/DM-XXXX/`. Archived folders are committed to git and serve as a permanent record of decisions made during implementation.

### Additional Context

Create additional files within `.agent/` when they help organise durable knowledge:
- Integration specifications
- API documentation
- Architecture decision records (ADRs)
- Testing strategies
- Deployment procedures

## Memory Bank Updates

Memory Bank updates occur when:
1. Discovering new project patterns
2. After implementing significant changes
3. When user requests **update memory** (MUST review ALL core files)
4. When context needs clarification

REMEMBER: After every memory reset, I begin completely fresh. The Memory Bank is my only link to previous work. It must be maintained with precision and clarity, as my effectiveness depends entirely on its accuracy.

When I receive a request, I MUST first check whether my memory bank is initialized. If not, I initialize it and set up the tasks needed to process the request.

## Commands

All commands are available as MCP prompts via the `dm` server:

| Prompt | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `/dm plan` | Validate Q&A in spec.md, generate phased tasks.md, open preview |
| `/dm implement-next-phase` | Execute all tasks in the next unchecked phase, then stop |
| `/dm implement-next-task` | Execute the single next unchecked task, then stop |
| `/dm update-memory` | Sync durable learnings from current ticket into core memory files |
| `/dm status` | Show current ticket phase progress |
| `/dm review` | Code review role |
| `/dm secure` | Security analysis role |
| `/dm test` | Test writing role |
| `/dm docs` | Documentation writing role |

